==English==

===Etymology===
From the root of {{der|en|la|Hispānia||Spain}} and the suffix {{m|en|-ic}}; compare {{m|la|hispānicus}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|en|/hɪˈspænɪk/}}
* {{rhymes|en|ænɪk|s=3}}

===Adjective===
{{en-adj}}

# Of or relating to [[Spain]].
# {{lb|en|historical}} Of or pertaining to the [[Iberia]]n peninsula, its people, its culture or its languages.
# {{lb|en|colloquial}} Of or relating to a [[Spanish]]-speaking people or culture, as in [[Latin America]].
#: ''Houses in New Mexico, California and Florida exhibit a strong '''Hispanic''' architectural influence.''
# {{lb|en|colloquial}} [[mestizo]].

